4\pi r^2
v = \frac{4}{3}\pi r^3 = 4\pi r^2 \frac{r}{3}= s \frac{r}{3}\ \Longrightarrow s = \frac{3v}{r}.
d\left[\frac{s}{t}\right] = d\left[\frac{s}{v}\right]\cdot d\left[\frac{v}{t}\right] =d\left[\frac{3v}{r}\right]\cdot d\left[\frac{v}{t}\right] = \frac{3}{r}\cdot 4 = \frac{12}{r}.
\frac{8}{r}
S=4\pi r^2
\frac{dV}{dt}=4
\frac{dr}{dt}=\frac{4}{4\pi r^2}
\frac{dS}{dt}=\frac{8}{r}
\frac{dS}{dt}=8\pi r\frac{dr}{dt}\tag{1}
\frac{dV}{dt}=4\pi r^2\frac{dr}{dt}.
